curl -XPOST 'http://localhost:9200/electronic_products/_create/2821' -H 'Content-Type: application/json' -d '{"product_name": "SGM48521", "table_name": "GENERAL DESCRIPTION", "content": "GENERAL DESCRIPTION  The  high-speed,  single-channel  low-side  driver  SGM48521 is designed to drive GaN FETs and logic  level MOSFETs. Application areas include LiDAR, time  of flight, facial recognition, and power converters using  low-side drivers. The SGM48521 provides 7A source  and 6A sink output current capability. Split output  configuration allows individual turn-on and turn-off time  optimization depending on FET. Package and pinout  with minimum parasitic inductances reduce the rise and  fall time and limit the ringing. Additionally, the 2.2ns  propagation delay with minimized tolerances and  variations allows efficient operation at high frequencies.  The driver has internal under-voltage lockout and  over-temperature protection against overload and fault  events.  The SGM48521 is available in Green WLCSP-0.88×  1.28-6B and TDFN-2×2-6AL packages.  "}'
curl -XPOST 'http://localhost:9200/electronic_products/_create/2822' -H 'Content-Type: application/json' -d '{"product_name": "SGM48521", "table_name": "FEATURES", "content": "FEATURES  ● 5V Supply Voltage  ● 7A Peak Source and 6A Peak Sink Currents  ● Ultra-Fast, Low-side Gate Driver for GaN and Si  FETs  ● Minimum Input Pulse Width: 1ns  ● Up to 60MHz Operation  ● Propagation Delay: 2.2ns (TYP), 3.6ns (MAX)  ● Rise Time:    WLCSP-0.88×1.28-6B: 500ps (TYP)   TDFN-2×2-6AL: 620ps (TYP)  ● Fall Time:   WLCSP-0.88×1.28-6B: 460ps (TYP)   TDFN-2×2-6AL: 610ps (TYP)  ● Protection Features:   Under-Voltage Lockout (UVLO)   Over-Temperature Protection (OTP)  ● Available in Green WLCSP-0.88×1.28-6B and   TDFN-2×2-6AL Packages    "}'
